# GitHub Secrets for iOS TestFlight
# Repo -> Settings -> Secrets and variables -> Actions -> New repository secret
#
# Required:
# APPLE_TEAM_ID                     Example: 2J6MSH6HG8
# IOS_PROVISIONING_PROFILE_NAME     Exact name in developer.apple.com (App Store profile)
# IOS_DIST_CERTIFICATE_BASE64       Base64 of Apple Distribution .p12
# IOS_DIST_CERTIFICATE_PASSWORD     .p12 export password
# IOS_PROVISIONING_PROFILE_BASE64   Base64 of .mobileprovision (App Store)
# APPSTORE_CONNECT_ISSUER_ID        App Store Connect -> Users and Access -> Keys -> Issuer ID
# APPSTORE_CONNECT_API_KEY_ID       API key ID (e.g. ABC123XYZ)
# APPSTORE_CONNECT_API_KEY          Full contents of AuthKey_XXX.p8 file
#
# Recommended:
# IOS_GOOGLE_SERVICE_INFO_PLIST_BASE64   Base64 of real ios/Runner/GoogleService-Info.plist
#
# Optional:
# IOS_KEYCHAIN_PASSWORD             Custom temp keychain password (defaults in workflow)
#
# How to base64 encode on macOS:
#   base64 -i Certificates.p12 | pbcopy
#   base64 -i TostuSahane_AppStore.mobileprovision | pbcopy
#   base64 -i GoogleService-Info.plist | pbcopy
#
# How to create App Store Connect API key:
#   App Store Connect -> Users and Access -> Integrations -> App Store Connect API -> Generate API Key
#   Role: App Manager or Admin
#
# How to create signing assets (one-time on Mac):
#   1. developer.apple.com -> Certificates -> Apple Distribution
#   2. Profiles -> App Store profile for com.tostusahane.tostuSahane
#   3. Export .p12 from Keychain Access
#
# Run workflow:
#   GitHub -> Actions -> iOS TestFlight -> Run workflow
#   or push tag: git tag v1.1.0 && git push origin v1.1.0
